
Clothing Store Website
![Preview](photo_5877223481550769890_y.jpg) 

This project is a front-end web application developed using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript as part of a university course. The main purpose of this project is to apply and demonstrate fundamental web development skills by building a simple e-commerce website for selling clothing items.

The website represents an online fashion store where users can browse through different categories of clothing products and view items presented in a structured and organized layout. The project focuses on building a clear and functional user interface using core web technologies without relying on external frameworks or libraries.

  Project Description

This application was designed to simulate a basic online shopping experience. It demonstrates how a static website can be structured to represent real-world e-commerce platforms. The project emphasizes clean code structure, proper layout organization, and effective use of JavaScript to handle basic interactivity.

The development process helped improve understanding of how web pages are built from scratch and how different technologies work together to create a complete user experience.

  Key Features

- Display of clothing products in a structured layout
- Organized product presentation for better user experience
- Simple navigation between sections of the website
- Basic interactive functionality using JavaScript
- Clean and minimal user interface design

  Technologies Used

- HTML5
- CSS3
- JavaScript (Vanilla JS)

  Learning Objectives

This project was completed to achieve the following learning outcomes:
- Understanding the structure of web pages using HTML
- Applying CSS for styling and layout control
- Using JavaScript to add basic interactivity
- Improving problem-solving skills in front-end development
- Learning how to build a complete small-scale web project

  Academic Purpose

This project was developed as part of a university coursework assignment to demonstrate practical skills in front-end web development and to gain hands-on experience in building functional web applications.

  Future Enhancements

- Possible improvements for this project include:
- Adding a backend system for dynamic product management
- Implementing user authentication and login system
- Enhancing product filtering and search functionality
- Connecting to a database for real product storage
- Upgrading UI structure using modern frameworks in the future

